== UserIDs ==

IDs in Discord identify users. They can't change.
How can you get someone's ID?
1. Go to Settings>Advanced. (Image 1)
2. Enable "Developer Mode".
3. Right click on someone's user, and click copy ID.
4. Done!

But what if you're in phone? It's easy, too.
1. Go to Settings>Behavior. (Image 2)
2. Enable "Developer Mode".
3. Tap on a user's profile picture.
4. At the bottom, tap "Copy ID".
5. Done!
